<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="High-risk_market">High-risk market</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vehicle_insurance_in_the_United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: High-risk market">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Insurers may be unwilling to insure drivers (especially at an affordable price) with particularly bad histories, which had led states to create "residual market" programs through which insurers are required to make insurance available. There are various ways that this is accomplished, with the most common being an <a href="/wiki/Assigned_risk" title="Assigned risk">assigned risk</a> plan<sup id="cite_ref-25" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-25"><span>[</span>25<span>]</span></a></sup> and other programs including joint underwriting associations, reinsurance facilities, and in the case of Maryland a state-owned fund subsidized by insurers.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vehicle_insurance_in_the_United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/SR-22_(insurance)" title="SR-22 (insurance)">SR-22 (insurance)</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mexican_insurance" title="Mexican insurance" class="mw-redirect">Mexican Insurance</a></li>
</ul>
